  "article_text": "Welcome to the Star Atlas weekly recap from the Intergalactic Herald. Below is what happened with Star Atlas this past week.\nWe are looking for guests to be on our podcast. The podcast is a discussion of the past week’s news about Star Atlas. If you are interested in being on the podcast, please contact us.\nWe are launching a Star Atlas merch store. Please check it out at Intergalactic Gear.\nWe are creating a “non-guild” guild. If you are interested in learning more, please go to Intergalactic Coalition.\nIf you would like to support our efforts, donations can be sent to intergalacticherald.sol\nSolana Game ‘Star Atlas’ Will Fill Its Galaxy With SingularityNET’s AI Agents\nDecrypt published an article about Star Atlas implementing AI agents.\nStar Atlas: How A.I. will be Incorporated into Gameplay\nBeyond the Horizon posted a video about a new AI partnership with Star Atlas.\nWeekly Star Atlas Newsletter #173\nAephia published their weekly Star Atlas newsletter.\nStar Atlas Space Exploration with No Loading Screens – A Look at Galia\nDominicVain posted a video showing space exploration in Star Atlas.\nASI Alliance x Star Atlas – Integrating Advanced AI in @StarAtlas\nASI Alliance and Star Atlas did a X Spaces chat.\nWhat Does Star Atlas Look Like Now?\nDominicVain posted a video of the current look of Star Atlas.\nStar Atlas Economic Report 2025 Q1\nStar Atlas published a new Economic Report.\nAtlas Brew #153 – State of the Star Atlas Community\nStar Atlas TV posted a recording of the latest Atlas Brew.\nStar Atlas Economic Forum – April 2025\nStar Atlas TV posted a recording of the latest Star Atlas Economic Forum.\nStar Atlas: Building a Gaming Cybernation from the Ground Up\nStar Atlas published an article about building Star Atlas.\nLatest podcast\nPodcast 176: Star Atlas Weekly Reviewby MattJuly 5, 2026In this episode, I recap the latest news of Star Atlas from the past week. Listen on Apple Podcasts Listen on Spotify I am looking for guests to be on the podcast. The podcast is a discussion of the past week’s news about Star Atlas. If you are interested in… Read more: Podcast 176: Star Atlas Weekly Review",
